Text.Value: Forgive the reception. Had some intruders a while back - can't be too careful.
Forgive the reception, eh, mate? Had some intruders a while back. Can't be too careful.

EditorData.NodeContext: Friendly, conciliatory - she's given you a hard time but only because she had to. Just doing her job.
EditorData.logicalname: HasMet if we convinced we're True Souls

Text.Value: Well, beg pardon but... it ain't just you the Absolute speaks through.

EditorData.NodeContext: Confused, hesitant - informing you that you are indeed special, but you're not the only one. Something you should already know.

Text.Value: I've got an audience with the one in charge.
You one of those Moonrise types, then?
I'm not here to talk to a lowly guard.
Cheeky bugger. Get 'em!
Then Minthara arrived. And now you - the Absolute's keen on drow, seems like.
Then the drow arrived. And now you - the Absolute 'as big plans for all of us, seems like.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wonder - this was a big turn of events.

Text.Value: A druid? Can't be sure - got one of 'em chained up below, though. Just follow the hollerin'.

EditorData.NodeContext: Muted, thoughtful - she can't answer your question but wants to help.

Text.Value: Aye, back the way you came now, afore I change my mind.

EditorData.NodeContext: Confident, sneering - acting tough, like she's letting you off the hook.

Text.Value: Right. Well. You ain't the first foreign type, I s'pose.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not expecting this, but keeping up a gruff exterior of command.

Text.Value: Ah, beg p-pardon! You must be 'ere to join the other True Souls. Please, go right ahead.

EditorData.NodeContext: Frightened and instantly cowed - you've just proved yourself to be a very high-ranking member of their new religion and she's terrified that she's overstepped herself.

Text.Value: All right, all right - normally, we'd stick you foreign types in the spider pit.

EditorData.NodeContext: Intimidated but trying to pretend you're just being prickly. Conciliatory, like you're making a big deal where you shouldnt'.

Text.Value: I want to see Priestess Gut.
*Your mind lurches, reeling suddenly as if... bitten.*
Still a bit strange, your kind running around. Absolute says we're all one side now though, eh?

EditorData.logicalname: HasMet if we convinced we're True Souls

Text.Value: *Your blood runs quicker, feeding the gnawing absence at the centre of your mind.*
You don't need to know about my business. Move.
Let. Me. Through.
*As the symbol glows, power courses through you. Authority.*
At first we thought it were just Boss Ragzlin and Priestess Gut. Just our kind, like.

EditorData.NodeContext: Explaining politely - something you should already know, but she's not about to question you.

Text.Value: Good to 'ave ya, True Soul.

EditorData.logicalname: HasMet if we convinced we're True Souls

Text.Value: She's through the main doors. Just follow the smell of burnt goblin-arse, heh.

EditorData.NodeContext: Getting bored, gesturing you on. Last line is a little chuckle to herself.

Text.Value: She's in tellin' the warchiefs wot's wot. Next raid's gonna be a big'un, I hear.

EditorData.NodeContext: Anticipating.

Text.Value: Like Priestess Gut and Boss Ragzlin. Gods, we even got a drow. Two, countin' you.
Like Priestess Gut and Boss Ragzlin. Gods, we even got a drow now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Said in awe of their new leaders, particularly the strange fact that they have a drow on their side.

Text.Value: Like Priestess Gut and Boss Ragzlin. Gods, we even got one like you now.
Like Priestess Gut and Boss Ragzlin. Gods, we even got a drow now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Voice awed as she talks about the great leaders blessed by this new god. (Pronounced DRAWER RAGS-LIN)

Text.Value: Already told you to bugger off, didn't I?
Oi! What's the bloody ruckus out there?

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed and on-guard - she's heard a great deal of noise outside and you, a stranger, have just stumbled in

Text.Value: Leave.
Your kind usually don't deal with Boss Ragzlin and Priestess Gut.
*A shiver runs across your mind... You feel sated.*
Well now, gonna 'ave to be more specific than that. We're drownin' in True Souls 'ere, we are.

EditorData.NodeContext: Chuckling at your naivete - you may have convinced your way inside, but you clearly know nothing.

Text.Value: We follow the Absolute and them She speaks through.

EditorData.NodeContext: Proud.

Text.Value: *The mark glows, but you feel nothing in response. Your illithid power is beyond reach until you rest.*
Gonna 'ave to be a bit more specific though, mate - Absolute's got a few favourites around here.

EditorData.NodeContext: Prickly, pedantic - you've just strolled in without any knowledge of their internal situation. She's always happy to pretend she knows more than you.

Text.Value: And... you and all now, I reckon. Go ahead, please - I'm sure you're expected.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hesitant, respectful - reminding herself that you're an important part of this new order.

Text.Value: Guessin' you're after Minthara. Could be 'er blood by the looks of you.
Oh no? Don't worry, mate - time for talk is well past. Get 'em!

EditorData.NodeContext: Mocking, utterly unintimidated by you and about to attack.

Text.Value: *The presence deep in your mind is awake, unblinking. This is it. A single word pervades your consciousness: 'Soon'.*
*A shadow swims across your vision, and a familiar voice tells you to be calm. You are loved.*
Oi! Only the Absolute 'erself gets to do that!
Who's in charge around here?
Oh! B-beg pardon, True Soul! At y'service, of course.

EditorData.NodeContext: Alarmed - she's just spoken sharply to someone who can kill her without a second thought.

Text.Value: B-booze. Bit much. Baffroom?
They seem ready to attack - be the one to strike first.
You what, you cheeky bastard?

EditorData.NodeContext: Incredulous that you'd talk to her this way, furious

Text.Value: *Your mind is full, bursting with ecstasy and terror. Finally, it is coming. You are becoming.*
Oi! Ain't no party in 'ere - we're doing the Absolute's work.

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed, affronted - she's lost her patience with people stumbling in from the party.

Text.Value: *The presence deep in your mind is awake, unblinking. This is it. A single word pervades your consciousness: 'Soon'.*
I'll be asking the questions.
Can't be 'ere to see the True Souls. Those types don't even bother to wait.
You 'ere to see Priestess Gut, Boss Ragzlin, or the drow?

EditorData.NodeContext: Ragzlin = RAGS-lin

Text.Value: Leave.
Then Minthara arrived. And now you - the Absolute's keen on drow, seems like.
Then the drow arrived. And now you - the Absolute 'as big plans for all of us, seems like.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wonder - this was a big turn of events.

Text.Value: Won't ask again - what's your business?

EditorData.NodeContext: All humour dropped - she's one step away from violence

Text.Value: *Your blood runs quicker, feeding the gnawing absence at the centre of your mind.*
*Your mind lurches, reeling suddenly as if... bitten.*
Why are you calling me a 'True Soul'?
I've got an audience with the one in charge.
Probe her thoughts.
State yer business. Now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Cold, deadly - the player has just passed through a party area, and this should be their first indication that the throne room is much more serious.

Text.Value: *Something stirs deep within you, hungry and alert... it's taking something you'll never get back.*
I've got an audience with the drow.
Leave.
*A shadow swims across your vision, and a familiar voice tells you to be calm. You are loved.*
Likes of you? Please. Only boss you need concern yourself with is me. Out. Now.

EditorData.NodeContext: Smug, arrogant - you're not important enough to get inside and she's turning you away with a warning.

Text.Value: *A shiver runs across your mind... You feel sated.*
...Well, I didn't say that. But you'll need to be more specific. Absolute's blessed us with three.
...Well, I didn't say that. But you'll need to be more specific, mate. Absolute's blessed us with three.

EditorData.NodeContext: Realises she's treading on thin ice all of a sudden. Tone is more reasonable than other branches.

Text.Value: The Absolute is gatherin' us all together. For something big, I reckon.

EditorData.NodeContext: Anticipation, confidence that their god has big plans for them

Text.Value: Was there a druid among these intruders?
*A strange symbol glows, marked on their flesh, and something within you stirs in response.*
But the Absolute says we're all makin' nice now. So in you go, I s'pose.

EditorData.NodeContext: A resigned sigh - it's against everything she knows to treat an outsider with respect, but it's what her new god demands.

Text.Value: *As the symbol glows, power courses through you. Authority.*
Leave.
It is loud. I think I lost my way in the confusion.
'Other' True Souls? What do you mean?
Do ya now? Might feel different once she puts a burnin' brand to ya.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tone is 'oh, really?' as if humouring someone who has made a grand statement.

Text.Value: At first it were just Priestess Gut and Boss Ragzlin. Then Minthara came along.
At first we thought it were just Priestess Gut and Boss Ragzlin. Then the drow came along.

EditorData.NodeContext: Explaining how things have changed.

Text.Value: *A strange symbol glows, marked on their flesh, and something within you stirs in response.*
Forgive my tone just now, True Soul. Had a few intruders a while back. Just bein' careful.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hesitant, subservient - she's just given you a hard time only to realise you're her superior.
EditorData.logicalname: HasMet if we convinced we're True Souls

Text.Value: That you have. Now - asked you a question, lovely. What's your business 'ere?

EditorData.NodeContext: Sweet, with a clear note of threat underneath - you're wasting her time.

Text.Value: Good for you. Turn back now and I won't spread yer business all over that wall.

EditorData.NodeContext: First line is cheery - follow up a much more threatening tone.

Text.Value: Well... cuz that's what you are, innit? One of them as hears our thoughts - and the voice of the Absolute.

EditorData.NodeContext: Confused, but nervously trying to be respectful. You've asked her a question you should already know the answer to, but she can't call you on it.

Text.Value: Oi! Get your lardy arse out of the doorway. Serious work goin' on in 'ere.

EditorData.NodeContext: Impatient, angry - you're wasting her time.
EditorData.logicalname: Player has come via side-entrance (not passed inner checkpoint)

Text.Value: Between the two of you, we're swimmin' in drow. Go ahead, I'm sure she's expectin' you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Toeing the line of disrespectul.

Text.Value: You think I can't tell true drunk from false? Mate, I been guzzlin' grog since the teat.

EditorData.NodeContext: Snorting, derisive - you're not fooling her.

Text.Value: *Your mind is full, bursting with ecstasy and terror. Finally, it is coming. You are becoming.*
Why are you calling me a 'True Soul'?
I'm here to see the True Souls. Do you want to keep them waiting?
You have - and I'm telling you to mind your manners.
*Something stirs deep within you, hungry and alert... it's taking something you'll never get back.*
You have - and I'm telling you to mind your manners.
Throne room's at the back. He's communin', mind, so step soft.

EditorData.NodeContext: Dismissing you, warning you to be cautious.

Text.Value: Well look, big-boots 'ere has an appointment with Dror Ragzlin hisself!

EditorData.NodeContext: Mocking, making a big deal (Pronounced Drawer RAGS-lin)

Text.Value: Outside, you bloody pisspot. Tell the rest of 'em to keep it down and all - work goin' on in 'ere.

EditorData.NodeContext: You've convinced her you're drunk and she's disgusted, worried you're going to soil the floor. She's trying to get you outside ASAP.

Text.Value: I've got an audience with Minthara.
I'll be asking the questions.
That was the sound of your friends dying. Care to join them?
'Audience' is right. She's an uppity one and no mistake, but she knows 'er business.

EditorData.NodeContext: Snorting at the drow's pretension, but acknowledging her power.

Text.Value: I'm here for Ragzlin.
Leave.
B-booze. Bit much. Baffroom?
You will let me in.
Who's in charge around here?
*The mark glows, but you feel nothing in response. Your illithid power is beyond reach until you rest.*
Well... cos that's what you are, innit? One of them as hears our thoughts - and the voice of the Absolute.

EditorData.NodeContext: Confused, but nervously trying to be respectful. You've asked her a question you should already know the answer to, but she can't call you on it. Her voice drips with awe when she describes your powers.

Synopsis: This goblin guard is aggressive and self-important. She's been tasked with keeping drunkards out and is taking to her small responsibility like a little tyrant, but will immediately roll over if the player convinces her of their authority.
